<br>
This doesn't exclude the possibility that there is a haste cap on pets, but it does seem to say that Cyricus's data is not conclusive. If this is the real problem then at least the solution is simple, make pets cast spells using the hybrid class delay rules. Has anyone else thought of this and has anyone done additional tests regarding it?<br>
<br>
Zalabim<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END-->This <!--EZCODE UNDERLINE START--><u>is</u><!--EZCODE UNDERLINE END--> an interesting proposition, and deserving of a renewed thread.<br>
<br>
Can we demonstrate this one or the other?<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> Razamatazz Pizzazz</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--><br>
